question: 名前
sourceMnemonic: Your <kanji>name</kanji> that's in the <kanji>front</kanji>. That is not your last name, that is your regular <vocabulary>name</vocabulary> or your <vocabulary>first name</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This word uses both kun'yomi readings (oh darn!). That being said, you've seen the kun'yomi readings for both the kanji that make up this word. The word <ja>名</ja> (<ja>な</ja>) and the word <ja>前</ja> (<ja>まえ</ja>) both are kun'yomi, so use those words and Voltron them into a single word, <ja>なまえ</ja>.
